Some Classic Definitions:

Cigarette - A pinch of tobacco rolled in paper with fire at one end and a fool at the other.
Love Affairs - Something like cricket where one-day internationals are more popular than a five day test.
Marriage - It's an agreement in which a man loses his bschelor degree and a woman gains her master.
Conference - The confusion of man is multiplied by the number present.
Compromise - The art of dividing a cake in such a way that everybody believes that he has got the biggest one.
Dictionary - A place where divorce comes before marriage.
Meeting Room - A place where everybody talks, nobody listens and everybody disagrees later on.
Classic - A book which people praise but do not read.
Smile - A curve that can set a lot of things straight.
Office - A place where you can relax after your strenuous home life.
Etc. - A sign to make others believe that you know more than actually you do.
Experience - The name men give to their mistakes.
Philosopher - A fool who torments himself during life to be spoken of when dead.
Atom Bomb - An invention to end all imventions.
Diplomat - A person who tells you to go to hell in such a way that you actually look forward to your trip.
Miser - A person who lives poor so that he can die rich.
Father - A banker provided by nature.
Criminal - A guy no different from the rest, except that he got caught.
Boss - Someone who is early when you are late and late when you are early
Doctor - A person who kills your ills by pills, and kills you with his bills.

'O' ALLLAH!

- When there is a violent storm and the seas are turbulent, the occupants of the boat cry out 'O' Allah!
- When the camel driver and the caravan are lost in the desert, they call out 'O' Allah!
- When disaster and calamity occur, the afflicted call out 'O' Allah!
- When doors are shut before those who seek to enter through them and barriers are placed before those who are in need, they all cry out 'O' Allah!
- When all plans end in failure, all hope is lost and the path becomes constructed 'O' Allah is called out.
- When the earth, vast and wide though it is, is straitened for you, causing your soul to feel constricted, call out 'O' Allah!

In fact, Allah is the first reality, the last reality, the end of philosophy and goal of all scientific thoughts. We must remember the favours and bounties bestowed on us which surround from above and below - indeed from every direction.

Updated Apr 21, 2019 1:15:07am
Apr 21, 2019 1:15:07am
Apr 20, 2019 7:05:39am
What is ego or egoism? The definition of egoism means sense of individuality or ethical theory that treats self interest and selfishness as the foundation of morality. Ego is the sickness of heart which makes the heart hard and rocky, it is an exposure of aggression and arrogance and an outburst of anger and displeasure. It makes one proud, audacious and intransigent, he/she thinks supreme over everything and everyone has to follow him and comply with his commands regardless right or wrong. When Islamic value remains absent from our daily life ego takes place in our hearts resulting in chaos and confusion, misunderstanding and mistrust between the spouses, siblings and close kith and kins. Selfishness takes place above everything and degradation and deterioration of morality prevails in our family and social life.

Ego is a fatal social disease, hence, Allah (s.w.t.) advises people in Surah Baqarah, verse 54 "Oh my people you must repent for your wrong doing to your creator. Yiu shall kill your egos. This is better for you in the sight of your creator." Therefore, we should not cultivate egos in our hearts or nurture and nourish them rather we have to kill them when we feel that we are suffering from ego problems. We must control our anger as differentia between man and beast is self control.

We have to thank our creator for all the blessings and bounties He has bestowed upon us rather than expecting people to appreciate us for our some good deeds. When we become submissive to the will of God our hearts naturally become soften. In the holy Quran it is mentioned that there are certain rocks when you hit them tears (water) roll down from their particles, even some rocks create fountain with flow of water, on the contrary, some human hearts are so cruel that your efforts fail to melt their hearts. Allah (s.w.t.) says, "You shall not treat the people with arrogance, nor shall you roam the earth proudly. God doesn't like the arrogant showoffs, walk humbly and lower your voice, the ugliest voice is the donkey's voice."

So let us kill our egos and make this world worth living with harmony, peace, tranquilly and serenity.

TRUST IN ALLAH THE ALMIGHTY:

You relax in an aeroplane though you do not know the pilot,

You relax in a ship though you do not know the captain,

You relax in the train without knowing the motorman,

You relax in the bus not knowing the driver,

*Why don't you relax in your life while you know that Almighty ALLAH is its controller?*

The bottom line is that as the poet says,

"Courage brother, courage, do not stumble
Though thy path be dark as night,
There:s a star to guide the humble,
Trust in God and do the right."

***Criterion To Be A True Muslim***

To be a true Muslim the most important precondition is that he must have an unflinching faith in Allah's existence and oneness of God, that Allah is the first reality, the last reality, the end of philosophy and goal of all scientific thoughts. He is the creator of this universe, He is the cherisher, He is the nourisher, He is the protector and He is the provider. A firm belief in oneness of God by heart and by expression is called Tawheed, or Iman. In a broader sense what Tawheed means is that, it is an indivisible oneness concept of monotheism in Islam. Disbelieving in this concept one will no more remain as a Muslim. This central and pivotal concept has been clearly mentioned in Surah Ikhlas, "Allah is one and only. He is eternal and absolute. He begets not nor He is begotten and there is nothing like Him."
In this Surah the nature and qualities of Allah have been indicated to us in a few words as one can understand. The first thing we have to note is that His nature is so sublime, so far beyond our limited conception that the best way in which we can realize Him is to feel that He is a personality, He is not a mere abstract conception of philosophy. He is very near to us. He cares for us. We owe our existence to Him. Secondly, He is the one and only God, the only one to whom worship is due, all other things or beings that we can think of are His creatures and is in no way comparable to Him. Thirdly, He is eternal without beginning or end. Absolute, not limited by time, place or circumstances. Fourthly, we must not think of Him as having a son or father, for that would be a humanly conception to us. Lastly, He is not like any other person or thing that we know or can imagine. His nature and qualities are unparalleled and unique.
Tawheed constitutes the foremost article of Muslim faith which is also associated with some other important elements on which also a Muslim must declare His faith, which are: 1) firm faith in all the prophets, 2) belief in all the religious holy scriptures, 3) heavenly angels, 4) resurrection, 5) destiny and 6) last day of judgement. One who has lack of belief in any of these elements will not remain a Muslim.
Apart from all the above, we must obey what Allah has ordained on us and abstain from those what He has forbidden for us. Among all His commands we must follow the basic priciples of Islam which are: 1) Iman, 2) prayer (salah), 3) zakat (charity), 4) fasting, 5) hajj (pilgrimage).
Just after Iman, Allah has given an emphatic impetus on prayer (salah). It has been proclaimed to all that on the day of Qiyama the first question will be asked about prayers. One who succeeds in answering these questions, rest of his other interrogations will be relaxed. So, without prayer we cannot attain the salvation of our souls. Prayer is known as the key to Jannah, without which the lock of Jannah will not be opened. There is a hadith that the curtain between Muslim and non Muslim is prayer, that a Muslim offers his prayer while the non Muslim do not. So, without prayer I cannot claim to be a Muslim.
In fact, prayer is the peace of mind, coolness of your eyes, remedies of your anxieties, curator of your diseases, protector of falsehood, hope in your disappointments, a ray of light in darkness, healing of your pain, a purifying element of your soul and moreover, extinguisher of hell fire and guarantor of paradise. Our life clock is ticking all the time, we do not know when it will stop. Once it stops we cannot restart again. Time is a great essence, so let us utilize our time in proper way. We must be grateful to the Almighty Allah for all His blessings and bounties, He has bestowed on us. There is a hadith "Intelligent is he who prepares himself before his death". Hence, we must be punctual to our prayers, which will protect us from torment of grave and hell fire and will enable us to be an eternal dweller of Jannah.
Prayer being a healer of diseases, Dr. Alexis Carell, a Nobel Prizeholder physician opined, "Prayer is the most powerful form of energy one can generate. It is as force as real terrestrial gravity. As a physician, I have seen men, after all other therapy had failed lifted out of diseases and melancholy through the serene effort of prayer".

Mahbub Khan shared a video.
Updated Aug 02, 2018 8:44:54am
Aug 02, 2018 8:44:54am
Road accidents have become a day-to-day incidents in our country. There is no any visible punishment or stringent action against those criminal drivers, who are responsible for these devastating accidents. So many valuable lives are being departed everyday due to their irresponsible and reckless driving. In some cases the killer drivers are arrested and brought to justice but subsequently they get release on bail and repeat the same accidents again. Most of the drivers have neither adequate experience of driving, nor minimal basic qualifications, nor valid driving licence. Then how they are driving? Simply under the mercy of the traffic personnel in lieu of the bribes. A couple of days ago it became viral in the social media that a 13 years little boy was driving a bus.
Sometimes, when people protest against the wrong doings of the drivers, the bus labour union goes on strike. There is one controversial minister in rhe present cabinet who also happens to be the leader of the Bus labourers Federation, supports the strike behind the screen. I do not understand how he can hold another public portfolio while being a csbinet minister.
As there is no any stern action against the killer drivers the rest of the bus and truck drivers become desperate and frequently make race and competition in driving and consequently make some fatal accidents. I believe Bangladesh is the most road accident prone country in the world.
However it is a good sign thar all the students across the country have become united and stepped up to the street spontaneously to protest the killing of the two bright students of Rsmizuddin Cant School and College. Today is the 5th day of their movement demanding exemplary punishment of the killer drivers, ensuring safe road and overall improvement of the traffic, infrastructure and transport systems.
However, the eventual good news is that on the eve of their relentless movement and indomitable resistance Government has now given utmost impetus and priority to this issue and going to take necessary pragmatic measures to imrove overall roads and traffic system.
We have wholehearted support to the legitimate movement of the students who are striving vigorously for a better and safe living for us and the future generation. We wish them every fruitful success in their movement. May Allah bless them and give them enormous strength to reach their noble goal.

Updated Feb 15, 2018 10:57:51am
Feb 15, 2018 10:57:51am
Feb 14, 2018 8:17:22am
Feb 14, 2018 8:17:12am
Feb 12, 2018 1:20:08am
The Muslim Character: As a Muslim, we should always be cheerful and pleasant. There are people who think that a perfect Muslim is simply one who is correct in the observance of the ritual prayers, the fasting, the zakah and performance of pilgrimage (Haj). This indeed is not the case but the basic elements of Islam. If the ritual performances do not help the person to be humble, virtuous and truly God fearing then he or she is not a real Muslim. A Muslim should be good and just in dealings with others, no matter their religion and take special care to keep away from all the shameful and sinful things that Allah has forbidden. We can summarize the teaching of Islam about the Muslim Character in this form:
- Be truthful in everything, don't lie
- Be sincere, don't be hypocritical
- Be honest, don't be corrupt
- Be humble, not boastful
- Be moderate, not excessive
- Be reserved, not garrulous
- Be soft spoken, not rude
- Be considerate, don't be harsh
- Be generous, not selfish
- Be chaste and pure, don't be lustful
- Be decent with others, don't be graceless.

These are a few among so many others.

Dec 28, 2017 8:41:27pm
SIGNIFICANCE OF THE WORD “ALLAH”: Vander Hoven, a psychologist from Netherlands announced his new discovery about the reading of Holy Quran and repeating the word “ALLAH” both on patients and normal persons. The Dutch professor confirms his discovery with studies and research applied on many patients over a period of three years. Some of his patients were non-muslims, others do not speak Arabic and were trained to pronounce the word “ALLAH” clearly, the result was great, particularly on those who suffer from dejection and tension.
It was published in a newspaper, which reported that the psychologist was quoted to say that muslims who can read Arabic and who read the Holy Quran regularly can protect themselves from psychological diseases. The psychologist explained how each letter in the word “ALLAH” affects healing of psychological diseases.
He pointed out in his research that pronouncing the first letter in the word “ALLAH” which is the letter “A”, released from the respiratory system, controls breathing. He added that pronouncing the velar consonant “L” in the Arabic way, with the tongue touching slightly the upper part of the jaw producing a short pause and then repeating the same pause constantly , relaxes the aspiration. Also pronouncing the last letter which is the letter “H” makes a contact between the lungs and the heart and in turn this contact controls the heartbeat.
What Is exciting in the study is that this psychologist is a non-muslim , but interested in Islamic Sciences and searching for the secrets of the Holy Quran. Allah, the Great and Glorious says, “We will show them Our signs in the universe and in their own selves, until it becomes manifest to them that this Quran is the truth.” (Holy Quran 42/53).

TRUST IN ALLAH THE ALMIGHTY:

You relax in an aeroplane though you do not know the pilot,

You relax in a ship though you do not know the captain,

You relax in the train without knowing the motorman,

You relax in the bus not knowing the driver,

*Why don't you relax in your life while you know that Almighty ALLAH is its controller?*

The bottom line is that as the poet says,

"Courage brother, courage, do not stumble
Though thy path be dark as night,
There:s a star to guide the humble,
Trust in God and do the right."

Value of Smile:

A smile costs nothing, but gives so much. It enriches those who receive without making poorer those who give.

It takes but a moment, but the memory of it sometimes lasts forever. None is so rich or mighty that he can get along without it.

A smile creates happiness in the home, fosters good will in business, and is the countersign of friendship.

It brings rest to the weary, cheer to the discouraged, sunshine to the sad, and is nature's best antidote for trouble.

Yet it cannot be bought, begged, borrowed or stolen, for it is something that is of no value to anyone until it is given away.

Some people are too tired to give you a smile. Give fhem one of yours, as none need a smile so much as he who has none to give.

Oct 31, 2017 5:26:01am
Quran Saviour in the Grave: According to an authentic hadith, when a man dies and his relatives are busy in funeral rites, there stands an extremely handsome man by his head. When the dead body is shrouded, that man gets in between the shroud and the chest of the deceased. While after the burial, the people return home, two angels, Munkar and Nakeer (names of two special angels) come in the grave and try to separate this handsome man so that they may be able to interrogate the dead man in privacy about his faith, but the handsome man says, "He is my companion, he is my friend . I will not leave him alone in any cases,. If you are appointed for interrogation, do your job, I can't leave him until I get him admitted into Paradise". Thereafter he turns to his dead companion and says, " I am the QURAN, which you used to read, sometimes in loud voice and sometimes in low voice. Do not worry. After the interrogation of the angels, you will have no grief ". When the interrogation is over, the handsome man arranges for him from All Mala'ul A'laa (the angels in heaven) a silk bedding filled with musk.
May Allah the Almighty bestow this favour on all of us. So Let us try to make some time to recite Quran everyday for the salvation of our souls and make a guaranteed place in Janna.

Updated Aug 05, 2017 6:18:45pm
Aug 05, 2017 6:18:45pm
Easy games never makes a man hardy, robust and firm. The plain and smooth sailing brings no credit to the sailor. On the contrary, the rough and perilous sailing makes the sailor expert and reliant and brings him a great credit and glory to life.
So, disdain the life of lethargy in action and procrastination in decision, the life without setting up any goal, the life without any aim and ambition, the life without any determination and challenges, the life where there is only false pride and vanity, rather embark upon a life where the inner significance of life means persistent struggle, perseverance, constant efforts and sincere dedication. Remember, the crowning glory of human life comes thorough works and struggle, aspirations and ambitions, dreams and visions. To achieve your goal there must be failure and success, as we know "Failure is the pillar of success." Dr. A.P.J Abdul Kalam, former president of India once said, "Don't give up your hopes if you cannot succeed in your mission, as FAIL means First Attempt in Learning, END means Efforts Never Die, NO means Next Opportunity."..
So, care not, the frowns of fate, the freaks of destiny and any unfortunate happening in your life. If fortune plays false with you today you try true for yourself tomorrow. Don't fold your arms and think all is lost but strive yourself and move all the while vigorously.
Of course, for our survival and better living we must work hard to achieve our goal in this competitive material world.What we are not doing for the sake of our glamorous living, a dignified status in the society, and a prestigious position in the organization, we are working tremendously to show our best performance to our superiors to attract their attention and entire satisfaction for uplifting the existing position, although we deserve it but sometimes due to company politics and favoritism we are deprived of the opportunity. It hurts our hearts but still we cannot fight for our right justice, we have to accept their ruthless decision with a broken heavy heart.
All what we are doing for our survival in this transitory world. We are working at least for 8 hours a day in our respective work places, we are spoiling a substantial amount of time in idle gossiping watching T.V programmes and entertaining movies, but do we ever calculate how many hours we are spending for Allah's sake, who has created us so beautifully with all the organs assembled and shaped in a proper and balanced way. Even we are so miser to spend couple of hours in 5 times prayer during 24 hours time. While we are indulged in idle gossiping, criticism and slandering takes place against others, while Allah has already warned us in Surah-Hujurat, verse no:12, "Don't speak ill of each other at thier back, would you like to eat the flesh of your dead brother? Of course you will abhor it." Backbiting is of that nature of sin. Once Ayseha (R.A) saw a very short girl and described to Prophet (PBUH) in her absence as a humor. Prophet (PBUH) warned her, " Ayesha what you are saying? If your words would be thrown to the sea the colour of water would be changed." But we never take into account of all these. behaviours. Remember, the favours and blessings of Allah upon us and how they surround us between the heaven and the earth-indeed from every direction. Health, safety, nourishment, clothing, air and water - these all point to the world being ours, yet we do not realize it. At our disposal we have two eyes, a tongue, two hands and two legs, can we picture ourselves walking without feet? Can we sell our ability to hear and see for the weight of Mount Everest in gold, our ability to speak for huge castles? Allah says in Surah-Bakarah verse no:152, "Remember me, I will remember you. Be grateful to me and don't reject faith." Just we have to close our eyes for a while and think that we belong to Allah and verily we have to return to Him and settle our accounts with him on the last day of judgement. So. we have to prepare ourselves for that day as this world is transitory and that world is eternal.

Updated May 23, 2017 5:02:24pm
May 23, 2017 5:02:24pm
***POWER OF PRAYER:
It has been about seven months I returned home after passing a long passage of time abroad, to settle down here finally. The very day I left for home, my eyes became brimmed up with tears, heart full of pain, expressions faltering, the pile of fondly memories stood up as an irresistible obstacle on the eve of my departure, but eventually he pleasure of "Home,home sweet home,there's no place like home", won over all those emotions.
however, I came back home, it was a wonderful surrounding of my family members, kith and kin and near and dear ones.This pleasure started to be fade soon as I couldn't adapt with the climatic and environmental change here, my routined, and a disciplined life which I maintained for so many years has ended up with a total mess of despair and frustration. In such a condition I was feeling myself as "a fish out of water" and consequently I became sick.
I was inflicted with severe pain in my left leg, which was sometimes unbearable to me and crossed the level of tolerance. Most of the time I was confined at home and my movements were limited between hospital and home. I had a bunch of plans in my basket which I wanted to implement one by one, all were jeopardized due to sudden illness which caused a serious sat back of my dreams. In such a critical juncture, I consulted with some neurologist and neurosurgeons, all they were of the same opinion that this pain was due to developing a gap in between the disks.They advised me not to undergo any surgery as I had a major surgery of the same nature previously, and also advised me to " Accept life as it is". The burning pain that I suffered and the ordeals I faced still seem to be a nightmare to me. Sometimes I would picture myself with those who have lost their legs and got frightened.
Long ago in a religious book i read,"Love of God and Prophet is mixed with poverty, calamity and diseases". I questioned myself do I really deserve love of god and prophet (pbuh) as I have not attained such spiritual insight or piousness? In surah baqara verse no:152-153 Allah (swt) ordained, " so remember me, I will remember you. Be grateful to me and don't deny me. O you who believe seek help through patience and prayer. Indeed, Allah is always with the patient."
Anyway, I envisaged that door of medical science is closed to me then why I do not knock the door of Almighty Allah, who is the most gracious, the most merciful, who is the first reality, the last reality the end of philosophy and the goal of all scientific thoughts, who has sovereignty over both the worlds. I set up my mind and used to touch my forehead on ground in prostration with divine supplication in tearful eyes at the depth darkness of night calling Him," Ya Allah,Ya Raab,You are the Lord of lords,King of kings,Emperor of emperors,You can do and undo everything. Please save me from my painful sufferings, please cure me, if you do not cure me no power on earth can help me." Eventually Allah (swt) responded to my supplication and miraculously I got cured (Alhamdulillah).
The saying of a Noble prize holder physician, Dr. Alexis Carell also inspired me. He opined, " Prayer is the most powerful form of energy one can generate, it is as force as real terrestrial gravity. As a physician, I have seen men after all other therapy had failed, lifted out of diseases and melancholy through the serene effort of prayer".

Updated Apr 22, 2017 5:30:00pm
Apr 22, 2017 5:30:00pm
Allah the Almighty created this universe and He endured men with a special place in His creation. He honoured men to be His Agent and to that end endued them with understanding, wisdom, conscience, self control and purified their love and affection and gave them spiritual insight so that men should understand nature, know themselves and know the creator through His wondrous signs and glorify Him in truth, reverence and unity.
Now what we find in our society, a question simply arises whether is there any reflection of His purpose of creation in human nature?? Love, affection, wisdom and conscience have been replaced with conflict of interest and selfishness, deception and deprivation, they choose the crooked path of discord and ends up with sorrow and pain, despair and disappointment, hatred and persecution and as such poison their lives, they boast in prosperity and curse in adversity, whereas Prophet (pub) used to say, "Poverty is my pride."
We all are surrounded by illusions, imaginations and emotions and always striving to be the happiest man in the world. But do we know the definition of happiness? Does it mean plenty of wealth and resources, bulk of money and valuable assets, a beautiful edifice and other luxurious elements? Not, not at all. I believe, happiness only can be attained through our humble submission to the Almighty Allah, who is our creator, sustainer, cherisher, nourisher, provider and protector. In whatever circumstances we are, if we pay our unalloyed gratitude to Allah and praise Him for His blessings and bounties on us only then we can be happy and attain our peace of minds and salvation of our souls. The hard reality of life and unflinching truth is that we have to leave this transitory world one day in order to dwelling in the eternal life, so why we are indulged in selfishness, illegal gains through corrupt practices, why we are making our society so disgraceful and polluted which will be the cause of curse to our future generation, while we know that our eventual goal is the "Grave" as the English Poet, John Gray said,
"The boast of heraldry, the pomp of power
All that beauty, all that wealth ever gave
Await alike an inevitable hour
The path of glory but leads to the grave".

Words fail to express how a mother renders significant contribution to each and every member of her family. How many sleepless nights she spends for her children, what a tremendous effort she makes in caring her children, do we ever count or evaluate her gravity of selfless sacrifice ever?? Does she do all these expecting any exchange or reward, never ever. A mother is always a mother, no worldly things can replace her. So those whose mothers are still alive they should always take care of them in their every trouble and adversity and especially in their old age. According to authentic hadith "Children's paradise are under the feet of their mother."

According to authentic hadith "Children's paradise are under the feet of their mother."

Mar 01, 2021 10:53:09am
EXPECTING GRATITUDE FROM OTHERS:

Allah the Almighty created human beings so that they may worship and remember Him and pay gratitude to Him for His favours and bounties bestowed upon them. He has provided them with sustenance. cherished them and protected them from disasters and helped them in every calamity and catastrophe. Nevertheless, many of them are ungrateful and unthankful to Him and worshipping others than Him and showing utter audacity of disobedience and ingratitude because the characteristics of ungrateful people are widespread in our society. So do not be dismayed when you find others who forget your favours and disregard your kind acts towards them. Some people might even despise you and make you an enemy for no other reason but you have shown kindness to them. Remember. When you help someone never expect any exchange which might be painful in the long run.
From among the ever repeating pages of history of father and his son. the former has raised him. fed him. clothed him. educated him. Inspired him. sweated and toiled his best for him so that he could get a very comfortable. loveable and glorious life with an elevated place in the society. All these sacrifices are quite selfless and only for the sake of his son's upbringing in proper way. But what we find around us today. some children are caring and respectful to their parents and some are so disobedient. disrespectful and cruel that they do not hesitate to send them to "Old Homes" where those wretched parents end up the last days of their lives mercilessly in sigh and sufferings. This is the tragic reality of their lives and these are the rewards of their sacrifice.
So be at peace if you are requitted with ungratefulness for the good you have done. Rejoice in your knowledge that you will be rewarded from the One Who has unlimited treasures under His disposal. This is not to say that you will refrain from performing kind and philanthropic acts towards others but the point is that you should be mentally prepared for ingatitude.
Let us say about our family life. A man always wants to spend the best part of his earnings for his wife. gifts her the valuables but when she finds any shortcomings she says. "What have you done for me during my married life? You have done nothing for me though there are some exceptions.
Here. In this regard there is a hadith when Prophet Muhammad (S.A.W)
returned from his travel of 7th skies
(Meraj). Ayesha (R.A) asked. What he had seen there. He replied. "I have seen so many people are being tormented in hell fire and majority of them are women. She enquired. What gravious sins did they commit? Prophet (S.A.W) said. "The only reason is that they
were ungrateful to their husbands".
Therefore. Knowingly that we are surrounded by ungrateful people do not stop performing charities to the poor and needy and always remember that the hand that gives is better than the hand that takes. There is a saying. "God helps him who helps themselves". In Surah Al-Hadid. Verse #11 Allah says. " Is there anyone who can give Me a sincere loan so that I can double it for him and grant him a magnanimous reward". Obviously Allah doesn't need any loan but by these words He has inspired His slaves to be charitable.
In conclusion I will say help the helpless and needy people but do not expect any gratitude. because if you expect and do not get the return it will harm you which will be very painful rather try to cultivate the nature of patience and digesting all the odds. Be mentally prepared that for example.if you give someone a pen as a gift. one day he may write with this against you or if you give someone a walking stick to lean upon and he strikes you with it as I pointed out earlier that most of the pepole are ungrateful to their Lord so what treatment you and I should expect.

GOOD MANNERS TO THE SIGHT OF ISLAM:

Everything that has gentleness in it is beautiful and whatever lacks it is spoiled. When you meet someone giving him a bright smile and a kind word, you are displaying a characteristic of the truly successful man that charms and attracts others. There are certain people whose personalities are like magnets attracting everyone who is nearby, simply because they are lived for their gentle talk, their pleasing manners and etiquettes and noble deeds.
Winning the friendship of others is an art that is mastered by those that are noble and pious, a circle of people constantly surrounds them. Their mere presence in a gathering is considered as a blessing and when they are absent they are missed and asked about. These blessed people have a code of conduct, "Repel the evil with one which is better I.e. Allah ordered the faithful believers to be patient at the time of anger and to excuse them who treat them badly."
It is narrated in a hadith that once a companion of Prophet Muhammad (S.A.W) came to him and sought his advice that how he could rectify him. Prophet Muhammad&nbsp; (S.A.W)
advised him to control his anger and uttered the same words three times.
They are those people who suck out malice from others with their sincerity, forgiveness and gentleness. They forget that was enacted upon them and preserve the memory of kindness received. Prophet Mohammed
(S.A.W) also said, :The Muslim is the person whose tongue and hand do not harm others and to whom his neighbours are safe. He also said, "verily Allah ordered me to keep relations with those who cut me off, to forgive the one who does an injustice with me and give to those who withhold from me.
However, remembrance.of Allah is the paradise on earth and whoever does not enter it will not enter the paradise hereafter. Remembtanc is not only a safe haven from the problems and worries of this world but it is also the short and
easy path to achieve eventual success and attain salvation of our souls and save our family, society and the nation as a whole from the verge of deterioration and the total destruction which is yet to come.

SOME VALUABLE SAYINGS ABOUT PROPHET MUHAMMAD (S.A.W.) :

He was born in Arabia in the year 570 C.E. (common era), started his mission of preaching the religion of Truth, Islam (submission to One God) at the age of forty and departed from this world at the age of sixty three.
During this short period of 23 years of his Prophethood, he changed the complete Arabian peninsula from paganism and idolatry to worship of One God, from tribal quarrels and wars to national solidarity and cohesion, from drunkenness and debauchery to sobriety and piety, ftom lawlessness and anarchy to disciplined living, from utter bankruptcy to the highest standards of moral excellence. Human history has never known such a complete transformation of a people or place before or since - and IMAGINE all these unbelievable wonders in JUST OVER TWO DECADES.
- Michael Hart

He was by far the most remarkable man that ever set foot on this earth. He preached a religion, founded a state, built a nation, laid down a moral code, initiated numerous social and political reforms, established a powerful and dynamic society to practice and represent his teachings and completely revolutionised the worlds of human thoughts and behaviour for all the times to come.
- Sir George Bernard Shaw

I believe that if a man like Prophet Mohammed (S.A.W.) were to assume the dictatorship of the modern world he would succeed in solving its problems in a way that would bring it the much needed peace and happiness.
- Sir George Bernard Shaw

How one man single handedly could weld warring tribes and wandering Bedouins into a most powerful and civilized nation in less than two decades.
"The lies (Western slander) which well meaning zeal has heaped round this man .... are disgraceful to outselves only"
"A silent great soul, one of that who cannot but be earnest. He was to kindle the world, the world's Maker had ordered so."
- Thomas Carlyle<br>

It was the first religion that preached and practised democracy; for, in the mosque, when the call for prayer is sounded and worshippers are gathered together, the democracy of Islam is embodied five times a day when the peasant and king kneel side by side and proclaim: "God alone is Great"... I have been struck over and over again by this indivisible unity of Islam that makes man instinctively a brother.
- Sarojini Naidu - famous poetess of India.

Updated Jun 27, 2020 9:02:14am
Jun 27, 2020 9:02:14am
TODAY IS ALL THAT YOU HAVE:

When you wake up in the morning, do not expect to see the evening - live with a belief that today is all that you have. Yesterday has passed with its good and evil, while tomorrow has not yet arrived. Your life's span is but one day, as if you were born in it and will die at the end of it. With this attitude you will not be caught between an obsession over the past, with all its anxieties and the hopes of the future, with all its uncertainty. Live for today.
During this day you should pray with wakeful heart, recite the Quran with understanding and remember Allah with sincerity. In this day you should be balanced in your affairs, satisfied with your allotted portions, concerned with your health and time.
Organize the hours of this day, do that you make years out of minutes and months out of seconds. Seek forgiveness from your Lord, remember Him, prepare for the final parting from the world and live today happily and at peace as there is a hadith. "Intelligent are those who prepare themselves before their death. Be content with your sustenance, your wife, your children, your work and every aspect of life.
Live today free from sorrow, bother, anger, jealousy and malice. If you have confidence in yourself and have a firm solid resolve, you will undoubtedly convince yourself of the following: "Today is my last day to live". When you achieve this attitude you will benefit from every moment of your day by developing your personality, expanding your abilities and purifying your deeds.
Keeping in mind all above let us take an oath that we wIll never cry for the past as it is dead, and we also will not heave a deep sigh for the future as it is dark and uncertain, so the best thing is to act in the living present, the day we live in today.

Dear friends, kith and kins at home and abroad:
My heartiest greetings and felicitations to you all on the auspicious occasion of holy Eid-Al-Fitr. May Allah the Almighty accept all our prayers and answer to our solemn supplications and Grant us a Magnanimous reward for the fastings which we have performed during the whole blessed month of Ramadan and forgive our sins of the past and bestow upon us His shower of blessings and bounties and keep us in peace with sound health and spirit until the next Ramadan again. This time we are going to celebrate Eid under enormous restrictions abiding by certain safety measures. Let us hope that the next Eid will be spontaneous, cheerful and above all in a Corona Virus free environment.
EID MUBARAK.

May 03, 2020 7:18:59am
FASTING IN RAMADAN:

Fasting is one of the aspects of worship that is done entirely for the pleasure of Almighty Allah in which a Muslim responds to the rulings of his Lord - the one and only, absolute and eternal - by abstaining from food, drink and sex appetite during the day whle fasting, believing that this obedience conforms to what Allah has ordained on us to validate the fasting and tuhis solemn act is only just to please his Lord.

Allah says in Surah Al Anam- verse 162-163 :Say: :"Verily, my prayer, my sacrifice, my life and death are for Allah, the Lord of the universe. He has no partner and that was what I was commanded with and I am the first of the Muslims". Hence, fasting is s divine sacrifice the purpose of which is just solely to please Almighty Allah and comply with His command.

In Surah Baqarah, verse 283 Allah says, "O you who believe, Fasting is prescribed for you as it was prescribed for those before you in order that you may acquire Taqwaa (piety)".

What benefits we can get from Feasting:
It prevents a person from committing what Allah hates like: lying, falsehood, backbiting, quarrel, idle gossiping, enviousness, pride and vanity and thus protects him from His punishment

Virtues of Fasting:

Some authentic hadiths are depicted below in support of Fasting mostly from Sahih Bukhari and Sahih Muslim:

1. In the blessed and holy month of Ramadan all the gates of paradise are opened and hellfires are closed and the devils are chained up.
2. If anyone stands for prayer and makes a sincere supplication in the state of Fasting his all the previous sins are forgiven.
3. There is a glorious and most powerful night during the last ten days of Ramadan where special emphasis has been given on 25th night as the holy Quran was revealed on 24th night (but still asked to seek on any of the last ten nights) which is better than 1000 months, virtues of the divine prayer on this night will be supermultipied, quantities are unimaginable.
4. There is a paradise named "Al Rayan" which has only been fixed for those who observed fasting during their life time. In the day of resurrection all will be asked to stand on a row and one by one will enter Jannah until the last one gets in and then the gate wIll be closed.
5. During Ramadan every night Allah frees so many sinners from hellfires as an amnesty in honour of Ramadan.
6. Fasting will act as a shield or protector from hellfire and will intercept Allah for his entry into Jannah.
7. If a person has shortage of virtues to qualify for Jannah then his sincere fasting and prayer will be taken into consideration to fill the deficiencies.
8. Fasting in Ramadan for a single day keeps him away from hellfires for a distance covering for a journey of 70 years.
9. In Ramadan Allah beautifies Jannah everyday and asks His slaves to beautify themselves.
10. Allah says Fasting is for me and other deeds are for him so I will reward him according.
11. Allah says during the time of Iftar no veil or screen remains between my slave and Myself and at this time no supplication is rejecited.
12. The bad smells which come out from the mouth during fasting seems to be the smells of perfume (Mask) to Allah (SWT).
13. Charity is another high ranking virtue in Ramadan. Allah says in Surah Hadid, Verse #11, "Is there anyone to give me a sincere loan so that I will double it for him and will give him a magnanimous reward.
14. Last but not least important is that there is a hadith prevailing in our country,
most of the imams quote in their speeches in Ramadan that first 10 days are for mercy, next 10 days for forgiveness and last 10 days for protection from hellfires is not authentic at all but totally fabricated rather mercy, forgiveness and protection remain constant from the beginning to the end of Ramadan.
15. Recitation of Quran is another most rewarding virtue during Ramadan.

May Allah accept our prayers, fastings and supplications and give us a glorious reward at the last day of judgement. Ameen.

COVID-19 IN ISLAMIC PERSPECTIVE.

In holy Quran it is mentioned, “Do they not see that every year once or twice they are tried with tremendous disasters yet they have neither any repentance nor they learn any lesson, nor pay any heed to turn to their creator” – S. Tawbah verse 126.
From the time immemorial if we look into the incidents which took place in different ages during the time of the prophets we will see a scenario of destruction of nations, their cultures and civilizations due to rejection in faith and aggressive revolts of their people towards the creator. Let us talk about prophet Noah (AWS) who invited his people for about 950 years to believe in oneness of Allah but hardly about 80-82 people established their faith out of the total population and prophet Noah (AWS) had to undertake immense sufferings and oppressions from his people. When they trespassed the bounds of their jurisdiction Allah punished them with a flood where all the people, except only a few who declared their faith in Almighty Allah were drowned and swept away. Verily, Allah doesn’t like those who trespass their bounds.
Prophet Salih (AWS) was sent to his people (Samud community) but the arrogant people didn’t listen to his message to believe in the existence of Almighty Allah, rather they put him in untold troubles and agonies and eventually all they were killed by a sudden earthquake in the position of upside down in the state of prostration.
Then propthet Lut (AWS) was sent to his nation when all were indulged in committing lewdness, Lut (AWS) showed to them the signs of our lord to give up their illicit practices and come back to the right path. But they ignored his call and eventually Allah rained down on them a shower of brimstones and all they were killed being shattered on the ground and as such Allah punished them who were indulged in crimes and sins.
(The above two incidents have been explained in Surah Araf verses from 73 - 80.
In Surah Araf also it has been mentioned in verse – 133, “So we sent plague, enormous deaths, locusts, lice, frogs & blood (in their food stuff).
Whenever Pherao’s (Feraun) people opened their utensils they would find frogs & blood everywhere, signs clearly self explained. Allah punished the people of Pharaon with years of droughts and shortage of crops that they might receive edmonition. Eventually all the disbelievers were drowned in seawater.
Now let us talk about COVID-19, a pandemic around the globe considering the number of death tolls & casualties, and its gravity of spreading so fast, UNO commented that since world war II, human civilizations have never witnessed such a disaster like corona virus before. Everybody is panicked and frightened that where we are going, where is our goal, what will be the ultimate consequence of the virus, what devastation is waiting in the lives of 7.5 billion people of this earth and in particular our beloved motherland, Bangladesh. All the powerful & resourceful countries like (so called superpower, mega power) are relentlessly trying to find out a way how to conquer this calamity. The opponent is not a weak nation that could have been silenced through the threat of nuclear weapons or ballistic missiles but just an invisible virus. The white House administration are totally upset and sweating how to tackle this disaster. The total civilization of 21st century is now at stake, people are helpless to the frowns and freaks of nature.
President Donald Trump in his statement on 27th Feb. said, in CNN “Corona virus is nothing, it will disappear very soon”. One of our political leaders also said a few weeks ago, “We are stronger than corona virus”.
Such audacious expressions only not make our creator angry but furious. So we should refrain from such statements.
As precautionary measures now “Lock down, quarantine, isolation, social distance” these words are prevalent in the current civilization, some of the systems which were first introduced by Prophet Mohammad (SAS) 1450 years ago. Regardless the superpower, NATO, EU, G7, first country to third country nationals all are now in the same platforms.
Bangladesh is a densely populated country and people are not law abiding who do not like to follow these measures. I wonder what consequences are waiting in the fates of 170 million people of Bangladesh.
Since this pandemic virus is taking away hundreds and thousands of lives every day and no medicine or vaccine has been invented as yet we must seek refuge from Almighty Allah and seek his mercy and forgiveness through our serene efforts of prayers and supplications before any worse comes up again. The present situation is the harvest of our sins and crimes, extreme social degradation, morally and ethically we have reached to the brink of deterioration, bribes, dishonest trading, gambling, child abuse, adultery, in name of modernity we are following western perverted culture and nudism, general and political killing, conflict of interest and wide spread corruption in all spheres of life.
O’ Allah now we are in the holy month of Ramadan. You are the possessor of Majesty, Magnificence and Might. Let comfort take the place of sorrow, make happiness come after sadness and let safety take place of fear.
O’ Allah your two holy mosques (Makkah & Madina) are deserted, congressional prayers are not held in the mosques. Please lift out the lock down and facilitate us to offer our prayers in mosques while we are in the holy month of Ramadan.
